"title": "6750: sin-bearer",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6750",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A person or animal that acts in God's sight in a substitutionary capacity, to whom are transferred the sins of others, together with the corresponding penalty for those sins.</p>\n<h2>The principle of accountability necessitates a sin-bearer</h2>\n<h3>All are held responsible for their own sin and its consequences</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:17\">LEV 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:1\">LEV 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:16-Lev20:21\">LEV 20:16–20:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:15-Lev24:16\">LEV 24:15–24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:19-Ezek18:20\">EZK 18:19–18:20</a></p>\n<h3>Individuals and nations come under God's judgment for their sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:4-Ezek4:6\">EZK 4:4–4:6</a></strong> <em>Ezekiel's behaviour foreshadowed God's judgment on the sin of Israel and Judah.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:58\">EZK 16:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:4\">EZK 18:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:21-Matt11:24\">MAT 11:21–11:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:12-Luke10:15\">LUK 10:12–10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18-Rom1:32\">ROM 1:18–1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:23\">ROM 6:23</a></p>\n<h2>God's gracious provision of a sin-bearer in the OT</h2>\n<h3>God takes away the sin of those who repent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:22\">ISA 44:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13\">2SA 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:12\">PSA 103:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:4\">ZEC 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>The sacrifice of an animal to remove sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:5-Lev5:6\">LEV 5:5–5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:1-Lev4:35\">LEV 4:1–4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:14-Lev6:7\">LEV 5:14–6:7</a></p>\n<h3>The Day of Atonement and the removal of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:8-Lev16:10\">LEV 16:8–16:10</a></strong> <em>The sacrificial goat expiated the sins of the people in the sight of God; the driving away of the scapegoat into the desert symbolised the removal of the sin of the community.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:15-Lev16:19\">LEV 16:15–16:19</a> <em>the sin offering</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:20-Lev16:22\">LEV 16:20–16:22</a> <em>the scapegoat</em></p>\n<h2>The function of the priests in the sin-bearing process</h2>\n<h3>The priests were responsible for the sanctuary</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:1-Num18:7\">NUM 18:1–18:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Strict regulations governed the performance of their service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:9\">LEV 22:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:42-Exod28:43\">EXO 28:42–28:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:17-Exod30:21\">EXO 30:17–30:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:3-Lev16:4\">LEV 16:3–16:4</a></p>\n<h3>The priests bore the sin of the people in a representative capacity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36-Exod28:38\">EXO 28:36–28:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:17\">LEV 10:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as sin-bearer</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ bore the sins of the world on the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:4-Isa53:6\">ISA 53:4–53:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10-Isa53:12\">ISA 53:10–53:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:14\">COL 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:11-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:11–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's intercessory role as high priest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:1\">1JN 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:25\">HEB 7:25</a></p>",
